Flow Sensor Meter & Display System - Pump Control
Pump Control Overview
The system uses a pump (or valve) to control liquid dispensing. The pump should run until the target volume (850 ml) is reached.
Component ESP32 Pin
Pump (via relay or MOSFET) GPIO 5
Flow Sensor Signal GPIO 4
Display (I2C) SDA=21, SCL=22

Control Options

1. Automatic only – Pump runs until 850 ml is reached
2. Button start – Pump starts on button press, stops at 850 ml
3. Button stop – Optional button to stop early. 
